definition.value: A homopolymer, composed of poly(phenylenevinylene) macromolecules.
A poly(phenylenevinylene) polymer, composed of poly[2-methoxy-5-(2'-ethyl-hexyloxy)-p-phenylenevinylene] macromolecules.
The calcium salt of oxalic acid, which in excess in the urine may lead to formation of oxalate calculi (kidney stones).
A poly(phenylenevinylene) polymer, composed of poly[2,5-bis(cholestanoxy)-1,4-phenylenevinylene] macromolecules.
A poly(phenylenevinylene) polymer composed of poly(p-phenylenevinylene) macromolecules.
A homopolymer, composed of polyfluorene macromolecules.
A commercially important azabicyclic antibiotic obtained from Streptomyces sapporonensis. It inhibits the Rho protein of E. coli.
The cation obtained from 3,6-diaminoacridine by methylation of the nitrogen at position 10.
A polyfluorene polymer, composed of poly(9,9'-fluorene) macromolecules.
An acrylic macromolecule prepared via co-polymerisation of alpha-D-Kdo-4P-O(CH2)3S(CH2)2NHCOCH=CH2 with acrylamide.
A poly(9,9'-fluorene) polymer, composed of poly[9,9-bis((6'-N,N,N-trimethylammonium)hexyl)fluorenylene phenylene dibromide] macromolecules.
An acrylic macromolecule prepared via co-polymerisation of alpha-D-Kdo-5P-O(CH2)3S(CH2)2NHCOCH=CH2 with acrylamide.
A tetrahydroxyflavone that is apigenin with an extra hydroxy group at position 8.
A poly(9,9'-fluorene) polymer, composed of poly(9,9'-dioctylfluorene) macromolecules.
A polyfluorene polymer, composed of poly(2,7-fluorene) macromolecules.
A poly(2,7-fluorene) polymer, composed of poly(fluorene-2,7-diyl) macromolecules.
A homopolymer, composed of omega-hydroxypoly(furan-2,5-diylmethylene) macromolecules.
A homopolymer, composed of poly(diallyldimethylammonium chloride) macromolecules.
A linear amino pentasaccharide comprising lacto-N-neotetraose having an alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl residue attached at the 6-position of the galactosyl residue at the non-reducing end.
The 2',4',5',7'-tetrabromo-5-isothiocyanato derivative of fluorescein; exhibits phosphorescence with an emission maximum at ~680 nm.
Any agent that acts on an opioid receptor or affects the life cycle of an opioid  transmitter.
Any agent that acts on a mu-opioid receptor.
Compounds that contain an amide group as a key feature of their structure and which have been used as fungicides.
Any agent that acts on a delta-opioid receptor.
A phosphocholine carrying an O-(4-diazoniophenyl) substituent.
Any agent that acts on a kappa-opioid receptor.
A xanthene dye with excitation wavelength of 544 nm and emission wavelength of 576 nm. Exists as an inseparable mixture of 5- and 6-isocyanate isomers.
An agent that binds to but does not activate an opioid receptor thereby blocking the actions of endogenous or exogenous opioid receptor agonists.
An agent that selectively binds to and activates an opioid receptor.

A methyl N-(2,6-dimethylphenyl)-N-(methoxyacetyl)alaninate that is the more active R-enantiomer of metalaxyl. A systemic fungicide, it is active against phytopathogens of the order Peronosporales and is used to conrtrol Pythium in a number of vegetable crops.
The 5-isomer of rhodamine B isothiocyanate.
The 6-isomer of rhodamine B isothiocyanate.
An aromatic diazonium ion consiting of a benzene core with diazonium and trimethylammonium groups para to one another.

An N(4)-glycosylated asparagine residue in which the glycan moiety is a branched undecasaccharide consisting of one D-glucosyl residue, eight D-mannosyl residues and two N-acetylglucosamine residues, one of which at the reducing end is bonded to the asparagine N(4) atom.
A homopolymer, composed of poly(diallylmethylammonium chloride) macromolecules.
A homopolymer, composed of poly(triphenylamine) macromolecules.
A homopolymer, composed of poly(propylene imine) macromolecules.

An N(4)-glycosylated asparagine residue in which the glycan moiety is a branched hexasaccharide consisting of three D-mannosyl residues and three N-acetylglucosamine residues, one of which at the reducing end is bonded to the asparagine N(4) atom.
A homopolymer, composed of polythiophene macromolecules.
A polythiophene polymer, composed of poly[3-(3'-N,N,N-triethylamino-1-propyloxy)-4-methylthiophene-2,5-diyl hydrochloride] macromolecules.
A polythiophene polymer, composed of poly(2,5-thiophene) macromolecules.
A poly(2,5-thiophene) polymer, composed of poly(3-hexylthiophene-2,5-diyl) macromolecules.
A poly(2,5-thiophene) polymer composed of poly(thiophene-2,5-diyl) macromolecules.
A polythiophene polymer, composed of poly{3-[(S)-5-amino-5-carboxyl-3-oxapentyl]-2,5-thiophenylene hydrochloride} macromolecules.
A polythiophene polymer, composed of poly(3,4-ethylenedioxythiophene) macromolecules.

An N(4)-glycosylated asparagine residue in which the glycan moiety is a branched decasaccharide consisting of seven D-mannosyl residues, one D-glucosyl residue and two N-acetylglucosamine residues, one of which at the reducing end is bonded to the asparagine N(4) atom.

An N(4)-glycosylated asparagine residue in which the glycan moiety is a branched undecasaccharide consisting of eight D-mannosyl residues, one D-glucosyl residue and two N-acetylglucosamine residues, one of which at the reducing end is bonded to the asparagine N(4) atom.
